              "https://www.micheledidier.com/en/artists/mel-bochner",
              "https://www.e-flux.com/announcements/150771/mel-bochnersinger-notes-1968/"
            ],
            "accuracyLevel": "normal"
          },
          {
            "possibleIdentity": "W. C. Bochner (William C. Bochner) was a chemical engineer or chemist active in the 1960s. He is known for co-authoring scientific research, such as the 1965 paper 'Esterification of Some Organic Acids with Isopropanol Catalysed by Cation Exchange Resin' published in Industrial & Engineering Chemistry Fundamentals. While Bochner himself is identified as a researcher in the field of chemistry rather than an artist, his active period and background in engineering align with the profile of technical professionals who collaborated with artists through the Experiments in Art and Technology (E.A.T.) organization during that era.",
            "sources": [
